---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Text Tools Hub"
  description="Privacy is our primary feature. Read the Text Tools Hub privacy policy: all operations run locally in your browser. We never collect or store your inputs."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <span class="bg-surfaceStrong text-ink text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.08em] uppercase px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full w-fit">
        Compliance
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-2 mb-3 leading-tight font-display">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[11px] text-muted font-mono">Last updated: July 12, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Privacy Callout -->
    <div class="bg-surfaceCard border-l-4 border-primary p-6 rounded-r-lg shadow-sm my-4 border-y border-r border-hairline">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider">Our Core Privacy Commitment</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-body leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Text Tools Hub operates entirely in your web browser.</strong> We do not transmit, upload, store, share, or collect any text, code snippets, numbers, or documents that you input into our tools. All processing logic occurs locally on your machine via JavaScript client engines. 
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-stone text-xs text-body flex flex-col gap-4 leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">1. Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>
        When you paste text, JSON databases, keys, lists, or draft messages into our word counter, case converter, duplicate remover, base64 encoder, JSON formatter, find/replace tool, or TTS engine, that content remains inside your browser session. None of it is sent to external API endpoints. Once you close your tab or clear the text box, the data is completely cleared from your device's memory.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">2. Cookies and Third-Party Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        We use third-party analytics and advertising networks to monetize our service and understand visitor flows. These third parties may use cookies or web beacons:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
        <li><strong class="text-ink">Google AdSense:</strong> Google uses cookies to serve ads based on a user's prior visits to our website or other websites on the Internet. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to users based on their visit to our sites.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-ink">Google Analytics 4:</strong> We collect aggregate, non-personal data regarding traffic volume, average stay times, and page transition flow paths. We do not correlate traffic data with user text inputs.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">3. Local Storage</h2>
      <p>
        We may use browser local storage (localStorage) to persist user configurations (e.g. remembering your selected text sizes or dark modes). These preference keys are completely non-sensitive and are stored strictly on your local device.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">4. Compliance and Security</h2>
      <p>
        Because our system architecture is stateless and databases do not exist, data leak risks are structurally eliminated. We cannot disclose user text histories to corporate or legal entities because we do not capture or hold them.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">5. Contact Information</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions regarding this local browser privacy policy, feel free to visit our <a href="/contact" class="text-text-link hover:underline font-semibold">Contact Page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
